Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.44,0:00:12.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah! The ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.36,0:00:14.86,Main,,0,0,0,,The ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.86,0:00:18.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Rika's gonna draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.08,0:00:21.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's my textbook!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:27.79,Main,,0,0,0,,This one is yours, Rika.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.79,0:00:29.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.13,0:00:30.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Textbook?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.67,0:00:33.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, are you going to study\Nwhile we're at the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.59,0:00:36.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, if I feel like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.26,0:00:37.43,Main,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.43,0:00:41.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Bringing study stuff on a\Nsummer fun day? Who even...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.18,0:00:45.23,Main,,0,0,0,,...does that...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.23,0:00:48.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Everyone enjoys themselves in different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.31,0:00:50.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Right, Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.11,0:00:51.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.61,0:00:54.95,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Mari will do a lot of studying,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.95,0:00:57.70,Main,,0,0,0,,and become a researcher just like her father!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.70,0:01:00.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.34,0:01:17.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, we're almost there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.48,0:02:52.23,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 8\NBell's Decision"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:54.32,Main,,0,0,0,,It's so big!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:55.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Isn't it extravagant?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.65,0:02:59.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you sure we can stay in this house?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.15,0:03:02.07,Main,,0,0,0,,My parents built it for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.07,0:03:04.45,Main,,0,0,0,,It's a waste if we don't use it now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.45,0:03:06.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, take care of Rika, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.87,0:03:09.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.62,0:03:12.96,Main,,0,0,0,,"Miwa"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:15.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Miwa? Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.42,0:03:20.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Are your parents from the Miwa Concern?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.51,0:03:22.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.09,0:03:25.51,Main,,0,0,0,,I never knew! So you're\Nvery wealthy, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.51,0:03:28.85,Main,,0,0,0,,My parents are my parents. I'm me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.77,0:03:38.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow! The ceilings are so high!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.28,0:03:39.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.24,0:03:43.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.78,0:03:45.20,Main,,0,0,0,,It really echoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:46.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Echoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:52.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka, want to explore the rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.58,0:03:55.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.58,0:03:57.63,Main,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.63,0:04:00.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you think I could, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.67,0:04:02.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Rika, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.93,0:04:06.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Could you look after Rika, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.43,0:04:07.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.72,0:04:09.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Rika, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.77,0:04:11.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:20.03,Main,,0,0,0,,It's lovely!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.03,0:04:22.44,Main,,0,0,0,,How many rooms are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.44,0:04:24.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I dunno!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.74,0:04:26.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, Rika, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:30.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Come on now! Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:32.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.04,0:04:33.54,Main,,0,0,0,,It's sparkly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.54,0:04:35.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.67,0:04:37.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Get me one, Rei!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:40.80,Main,,0,0,0,,I think it's too high for me to reach...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.80,0:04:44.05,Main,,0,0,0,,The blue sky, the shining sea. It's so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.05,0:04:46.18,Main,,0,0,0,,The salt air brushing my cheeks...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.18,0:04:49.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Summer days spent at an extravagant villa...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.47,0:04:53.14,Main,,0,0,0,,But why couldn't that jerk have come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:54.35,Main,,0,0,0,,You mean Futa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.35,0:04:55.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.69,0:04:58.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka, you invited him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.44,0:05:01.36,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.36,0:05:04.78,Main,,0,0,0,,He said no because he had a soccer match.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.41,0:05:10.58,Main,,0,0,0,,It's hard being far away and\Nnot getting to see each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.58,0:05:14.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, now, you'll see him again\Nwhen school starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.29,0:05:16.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:20.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Ma'am, isn't it hard for you, not\Nseeing your husband for three years?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:21.50,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:22.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.84,0:05:24.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:27.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, we met while I was abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.30,0:05:31.43,Main,,0,0,0,,And when he went back\Nto Japan, I stayed in Paris,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.43,0:05:33.93,Main,,0,0,0,,so we've gone a year at a time\Nwithout seeing each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.93,0:05:36.60,Main,,0,0,0,,A year? You're so strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.60,0:05:37.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:42.52,Main,,0,0,0,,He loves to be free, and hates\Ncarrying things like cell phones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.52,0:05:44.90,Main,,0,0,0,,So I'm used to not being in touch with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.90,0:05:47.95,Main,,0,0,0,,What? He doesn't even have a cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.95,0:05:50.74,Main,,0,0,0,,He never carries one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:54.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Never carries a cell phone?\NHow old-fashioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:56.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:06:00.13,Main,,0,0,0,,But cell phones are a\Nrelatively recent invention.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.13,0:06:02.21,Main,,0,0,0,,So I find that rather normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.21,0:06:03.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:06.63,Main,,0,0,0,,When I was young, my husband\Ndidn't have a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:11.80,Main,,0,0,0,,We'd end up waiting on either side of the\NHachiko statue without seeing each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.80,0:06:13.56,Main,,0,0,0,,That close?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.56,0:06:14.77,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:17.52,Main,,0,0,0,,I think that's because you're you, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:19.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:25.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I wonder what Papa's doing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.61,0:06:33.08,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1876\N(What is Now) Boston, America"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:39.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you catching a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.08,0:06:42.50,Main,,0,0,0,,I think someone's spreading rumors about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.50,0:06:44.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.34,0:06:48.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for\Ncoming to view our classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:50.18,Main,,0,0,0,,The honor is all mine, Mr. Bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:54.39,Main,,0,0,0,,The visible speech system your father\Ninvented was truly incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:56.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, let's try speaking together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.85,0:07:06.15,Main,,0,0,0,,--"One good turn deserves another."\N--"One good turn deserves another."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:10.49,Main,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't think those children were deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.78,0:07:14.41,Main,,0,0,0,,I would love to bring it back to Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:17.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Could I have a few of your books?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.16,0:07:20.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Certainly, Your Majesty!\NI'll send them to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.75,0:07:23.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Please, call me Dom Pedro.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:25.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Dom Pedro, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.55,0:07:31.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Mabel, your fiance is--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:32.80,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.72,0:07:35.35,Main,,0,0,0,,The emperor's addressing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:38.22,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.22,0:07:40.52,Main,,0,0,0,,She's hard of hearing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:43.69,Main,,0,0,0,,If she can't see your lips,\Nshe can't understand what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:45.27,Main,,0,0,0,,I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.27,0:07:48.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Beautiful lady, I must be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.03,0:07:53.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Excellent work, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.86,0:07:55.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, let's head back to the classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:57.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.04,0:08:02.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your help before, Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:04.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:05.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Doctor Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.83,0:08:08.80,Main,,0,0,0,,You came all the way from Japan\Nto see our classes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.80,0:08:10.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, I saw that code of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.80,0:08:13.76,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought it might be useful for learning\Npronunciation in different languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:16.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Exactly! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.60,0:08:17.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:20.72,Main,,0,0,0,,That's a rather strong handshake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.72,0:08:23.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry.\NI wasn't thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.11,0:08:29.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Mabel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.32,0:08:33.28,Main,,0,0,0,,It's a telegram from Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:35.41,Main,,0,0,0,,From Mr. Hubbard?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.41,0:08:37.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.07,0:08:42.37,Main,,0,0,0,,He wants you to attend\Nthe exposition, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:46.92,Main,,0,0,0,,But I told him it was impossible, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.92,0:08:52.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Alex, they're holding the\NCentennial Exposition in Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.63,0:08:55.97,Main,,0,0,0,,I made special arrangements\Nso that you could exhibit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.97,0:08:58.26,Main,,0,0,0,,that telephone you developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.26,0:08:59.89,Main,,0,0,0,,My telephone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.89,0:09:04.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course, you can display\Nyour visual speech along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.35,0:09:07.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Isn't that wonderful, Dr. Bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.19,0:09:09.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.27,0:09:11.28,Main,,0,0,0,,If you demonstrate it at the exhibition,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.28,0:09:15.49,Main,,0,0,0,,it will spread awareness of the telephone,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:18.20,Main,,0,0,0,,and you'll likely be able\Nto make a business of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:22.12,Main,,0,0,0,,If you can do that, I'll officially\Nallow your marriage to my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.12,0:09:24.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.04,0:09:28.42,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, sir, but that invention\Nhas room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:33.51,Main,,0,0,0,,And I can't neglect my school\Nto perform the needed experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.51,0:09:37.34,Main,,0,0,0,,You still haven't changed your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:39.47,Main,,0,0,0,,I told you before:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.47,0:09:43.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Until I have enough people\Nthat I can entrust this work to,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.47,0:09:46.02,Main,,0,0,0,,I cannot abandon my work as a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.02,0:09:48.73,Main,,0,0,0,,He who runs after two hares\Nwill catch neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:51.86,Main,,0,0,0,,You should focus on promoting the telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.86,0:09:55.99,Main,,0,0,0,,But they're both important to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.16,0:10:01.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I'll go to the exhibition myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:04.45,Main,,0,0,0,,You'll allow me to display it, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.45,0:10:05.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.91,0:10:07.91,Main,,0,0,0,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.91,0:10:13.05,Main,,0,0,0,,He said that the display alone\Nmight not make the pitch to the judges.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.05,0:10:15.30,Main,,0,0,0,,That wasn't what we discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.30,0:10:16.30,Main,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.59,0:10:19.01,Main,,0,0,0,,We'll talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.68,0:10:27.39,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to do this in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:30.23,Main,,0,0,0,,No, I suppose we're both having trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:31.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Both?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.90,0:10:34.48,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm also the type to follow my own path,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.48,0:10:37.74,Main,,0,0,0,,no matter what my wife says to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.07,0:10:42.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Even if you love your wife? I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.66,0:10:45.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess they're different situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.41,0:10:48.21,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.21,0:10:51.12,Main,,0,0,0,,I love Mabel from the bottom of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.12,0:10:56.63,Main,,0,0,0,,But I just can't bring myself\Nto agree with her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:11:00.05,Main,,0,0,0,,In life, the question of what to prioritize
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:03.72,Main,,0,0,0,,might be the eternal conflict,\Nno matter how the era might change.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.72,0:11:04.76,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.76,0:11:07.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I mean, do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.06,0:11:09.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bell, I'll be rooting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.85,0:11:11.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.77,0:11:17.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Was the wedding in Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.98,0:11:22.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. And the day after that,\Nhe went away for six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:25.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Six months?! He's gone missing before, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:26.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:28.95,Main,,0,0,0,,And this time it's three years?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.95,0:11:30.71,Main,,0,0,0,,That man of mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.71,0:11:34.33,Main,,0,0,0,,But at least he's grown up\Nenough to leave me a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.33,0:11:37.75,Main,,0,0,0,,He'd been missing for four or five days,\Nso I went to his laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.75,0:11:41.76,Main,,0,0,0,,and found out he'd gone on a research trip.\NExhausting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:48.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, does that book have\Nsomething to do with his research?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.23,0:11:56.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, does that book have\Nsomething to do with his research?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.82,0:12:00.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh... I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:04.61,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. That brings a lot\Nof things together, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.61,0:12:05.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.16,0:12:06.74,Main,,0,0,0,,What things?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.74,0:12:10.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing. Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:13.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, why don't we go swimming?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.25,0:12:14.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.00,0:12:16.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go swimming!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:21.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.21,0:12:23.22,Main,,0,0,0,,That's grammatically incorrect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:24.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Incorrect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:35.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.85,0:12:36.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.69,0:12:41.94,Main,,0,0,0,,So you are here, Mrs. Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:45.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Fancy meeting you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.16,0:12:47.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.12,0:12:48.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.12,0:12:53.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Your new almond praline\Ncream puffs were delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.54,0:12:55.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your continued patronage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.88,0:12:59.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Are those your children?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.38,0:13:00.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.17,0:13:05.63,Main,,0,0,0,,This is Mr. Mikage, a customer at our store.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.63,0:13:06.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:07.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.80,0:13:08.97,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm a friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.97,0:13:10.43,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm Mizuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.89,0:13:15.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. It is summer vacation, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.19,0:13:19.73,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right. If I might,\Nwould you like to join me on a cruise?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:21.36,Main,,0,0,0,,A cruise?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.36,0:13:23.86,Main,,0,0,0,,I have a cabin cruiser at the marina.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:27.41,Main,,0,0,0,,As long as you're here,\Nwhy don't we make a party of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.41,0:13:28.37,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.37,0:13:30.53,Main,,0,0,0,,My, I'd love to!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:31.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.70,0:13:36.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry. I've just never\Nbeen on a cabin cruiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.71,0:13:39.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama, what's a cabin cruiser?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.79,0:13:41.25,Main,,0,0,0,,It's a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.25,0:13:44.26,Main,,0,0,0,,A boat! I wanna ride!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.26,0:13:47.55,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm glad. Then why don't you all join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:52.68,Main,,0,0,0,,If you insist, then we ladies\Nshall accompany you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:55.31,Main,,0,0,0,,You're getting too carried away, Waka.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.31,0:13:57.85,Main,,0,0,0,,I just felt like acting like a lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.85,0:14:01.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka, you could be an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:02.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:05.40,Main,,0,0,0,,But I'm gonna be a TV announcer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.40,0:14:07.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Really? I didn't know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.86,0:14:09.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Because I never told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.03,0:14:17.83,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. So you have a real dream, huh, Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.83,0:14:20.96,Main,,0,0,0,,And Shun, you want to be a doctor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:21.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.96,0:14:29.93,Main,,0,0,0,,But lately, I've started to think\Nthere might be other possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.93,0:14:32.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? You won't become a doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:34.43,Main,,0,0,0,,They're just possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.43,0:14:35.81,Main,,0,0,0,,I might be a researcher.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.81,0:14:38.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh? Like Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.85,0:14:42.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, Mari, you work hard, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.11,0:14:46.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't even know what I wanna be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.24,0:14:53.99,Main,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this, Mabel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.99,0:14:56.79,Main,,0,0,0,,I came because you said\Nyou had something to show me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.79,0:14:59.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Please, get on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:03.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Give the demonstration\Nat the exhibition, like Father wants!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.71,0:15:05.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Mabel...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.17,0:15:09.22,Main,,0,0,0,,I won't be able to marry you if you don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.55,0:15:14.68,Main,,0,0,0,,But you know very well that I have school...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.68,0:15:16.56,Main,,0,0,0,,The school will still be here\Nwhen you get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.56,0:15:19.23,Main,,0,0,0,,But this exhibition will only come once.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.53,0:15:30.20,Main,,0,0,0,,You're getting on, aren't you, Mr. Bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.20,0:15:31.57,Main,,0,0,0,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.57,0:15:33.32,Main,,0,0,0,,You'd better hurry. Go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.49,0:15:37.41,Main,,0,0,0,,I understand, Mabel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.41,0:15:40.04,Main,,0,0,0,,But I'm still pursuing those two hares.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.38,0:15:44.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.76,0:15:50.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bell! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:04.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Dr. Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.44,0:16:07.86,Main,,0,0,0,,You always show up when Mabel needs you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.86,0:16:09.78,Main,,0,0,0,,You're like her knight in shining armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.78,0:16:13.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I just felt like history might change
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:16.32,Main,,0,0,0,,if you didn't get on this train.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.32,0:16:18.16,Main,,0,0,0,,History?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.16,0:16:22.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, no matter how I try\Nto protect the flow of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:26.04,Main,,0,0,0,,some things may yet remain part of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.04,0:16:27.92,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.92,0:16:30.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing. Just talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.76,0:16:33.59,Main,,0,0,0,,But you can't fight a woman's tears, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.59,0:16:37.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Does that go for your wife's tears, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.35,0:16:39.18,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.18,0:16:42.35,Main,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen her tears in quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.48,0:16:53.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.53,0:16:55.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.28,0:16:58.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I was just thinking about Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:00.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.24,0:17:05.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa proposed to me on a beach near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.04,0:17:07.29,Main,,0,0,0,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.29,0:17:11.13,Main,,0,0,0,,He said that if you swear your love\Nin front of that setting sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:13.51,Main,,0,0,0,,it will last forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.51,0:17:16.84,Main,,0,0,0,,He'd made it all up, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.84,0:17:18.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:21.26,Main,,0,0,0,,But he said humans create\Nwhatever they imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.26,0:17:24.10,Main,,0,0,0,,and so he was going to create that legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:28.77,Main,,0,0,0,,I wonder what he's doing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.77,0:17:30.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.45,0:17:38.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, everyone, eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.28,0:17:41.83,Main,,0,0,0,,The meat has cooked up nicely. Help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.66,0:17:43.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:45.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.62,0:17:47.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:49.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I meant Mrs. Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.67,0:17:53.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Shall I call you Akira, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.17,0:17:54.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.67,0:18:00.26,Main,,0,0,0,,I was wondering. Would you like to\Nwork on developing premium desserts?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.26,0:18:02.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Premium desserts?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.43,0:18:07.39,Main,,0,0,0,,I know a lot of gourmets\Nfor whom money is no object.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.39,0:18:13.07,Main,,0,0,0,,If you leave it to me, I could\Nexpand your business even further.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.07,0:18:14.90,Main,,0,0,0,,I bet you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.90,0:18:18.95,Main,,0,0,0,,And of course, I'm very focused on my art.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.95,0:18:20.87,Main,,0,0,0,,But I want to offer my sweets
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.87,0:18:24.95,Main,,0,0,0,,at reasonable prices,\Nso everyone can enjoy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:27.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that a no, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.12,0:18:29.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.12,0:18:31.33,Main,,0,0,0,,There's no ambiguity with you, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.33,0:18:34.67,Main,,0,0,0,,That guy's pretty hot, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.67,0:18:37.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes. If I were a single woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.84,0:18:41.34,Main,,0,0,0,,No way! Mom, is he your type?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.34,0:18:44.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, he's very handsome, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.14,0:18:48.89,Main,,0,0,0,,So Waka and her mom\Nlike that kind of guy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.89,0:18:50.60,Main,,0,0,0,,You don't, Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:53.82,Main,,0,0,0,,I didn't say that, exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.82,0:18:55.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.19,0:18:58.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:19:00.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Eat your fill. There's no need to hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.91,0:19:03.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I will. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.37,0:19:05.45,Main,,0,0,0,,What the heck...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:10.21,Main,,0,0,0,,That's a lovely necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:11.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.37,0:19:14.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:17.05,Main,,0,0,0,,She got it from Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.05,0:19:19.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.72,0:19:32.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Ms. Kuroki, we're out of meat,\Nso could you move this out of the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.35,0:19:33.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.73,0:19:34.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Talk to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:35.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.49,0:19:43.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.62,0:19:47.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, could you get a change\Nof clothes for Rika from my bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.58,0:19:49.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.27,0:20:17.98,Main,,0,0,0,,That lady... She was trying to steal it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.11,0:20:20.82,Main,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:30.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:34.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Shall I?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.67,0:20:36.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.17,0:20:39.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, did you bring them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:40.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.51,0:20:43.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.76,0:20:48.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, you look very young.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.39,0:20:53.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, I'm borrowing your book.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.81,0:21:00.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Seriously... Shun's way too gullible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.15,0:21:01.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Just because she's pretty--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.90,0:21:05.91,Main,,0,0,0,,That hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:08.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Darn it! Stupid Shun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.80,0:21:32.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Did you hear something just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.18,0:21:33.18,Main,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.78,0:21:46.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh no! I'm transporting!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.78,0:21:48.87,Main,,0,0,0,,What do I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.24,0:21:51.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.88,0:22:01.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.59,0:22:04.21,Main,,0,0,0,,What?! Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.31,0:22:21.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Where am I? Whose page did I travel into?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.15,0:22:26.15,Main,,0,0,0,,What do I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.15,0:22:27.95,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode: Bell's Responses"\NWhat do I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.95,0:22:30.07,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode: Bell's Responses"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.16,0:24:00.66,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:03.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.08,0:24:04.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.29,0:24:05.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.96,0:24:08.13,Main,,0,0,0,,It's a speaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.13,0:24:11.42,Main,,0,0,0,,The foundation of the\Ntelephone that Bell invented
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.42,0:24:15.09,Main,,0,0,0,,is a connected pair of speakers like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.09,0:24:17.81,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not a microphone and a speaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.81,0:24:20.98,Main,,0,0,0,,The principle of the microphone\Nand speaker is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.98,0:24:24.90,Main,,0,0,0,,So when you speak into one of the speakers...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.90,0:24:29.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.23,0:24:33.24,Main,,0,0,0,,You're right! You can send\Nthe voice between speakers!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.24,0:24:35.57,Main,,0,0,0,,What's the principle behind it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.57,0:24:36.28,Main,,0,0,0,,"Sound is produced"\N"Vibrations in air"\N"Eardrum interprets the vibrations as sound"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.28,0:24:39.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you know how hearing works?\N"Sound is produced"\N"Vibrations in air"\N"Eardrum interprets the vibrations as sound"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.20,0:24:43.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, you speak, and the air vibrates,\N"Sound is produced"\N"Vibrations in air"\N"Eardrum interprets the vibrations as sound"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.37,0:24:48.04,Main,,0,0,0,,and that makes your eardrum shake,\Nand then you can hear it, right?\N"Sound is produced"\N"Vibrations in air"\N"Eardrum interprets the vibrations as sound"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.04,0:24:49.38,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right.\N"Sound is produced"\N"Vibrations in air"\N"Eardrum interprets the vibrations as sound"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.38,0:24:54.51,Main,,0,0,0,,It was Bell who thought of mechanically\Nconverting that into electric signals.\N"Sound is produced"\N"Vibrations in air"\N"Eardrum interprets the vibrations as sound"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.51,0:24:55.30,Main,,0,0,0,,"Transmitter"\N"Receiver"\N"Coil" "Electric current" "Magnet" "Paper cone (Diaphragm)"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.30,0:24:59.76,Main,,0,0,0,,On the speaker's end, the voice makes the\Ndiaphragm shake, causing the coils to move.\N"Transmitter"\N"Receiver"\N"Coil" "Electric current" "Magnet" "Paper cone (Diaphragm)"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.76,0:25:01.72,Main,,0,0,0,,This causes an electric current.\N"Transmitter"\N"Receiver"\N"Coil" "Electric current" "Magnet" "Paper cone (Diaphragm)"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.72,0:25:05.73,Main,,0,0,0,,In other words, it's changed\Nthe sound into an electric signal.\N"Transmitter"\N"Receiver"\N"Coil" "Electric current" "Magnet" "Paper cone (Diaphragm)"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.73,0:25:08.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Just like the electromagnetic induction\Nwe did with Mr. Faraday?\N"Transmitter"\N"Receiver"\N"Coil" "Electric current" "Magnet" "Paper cone (Diaphragm)"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.65,0:25:13.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. Then the coil on the receiver's end\Nreacts to the electric signal,\N"Transmitter"\N"Receiver"\N"Coil" "Electric current" "Magnet" "Paper cone (Diaphragm)"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.57,0:25:16.49,Main,,0,0,0,,and the diaphragm vibrates and creates sound.\N"Transmitter"\N"Receiver"\N"Coil" "Electric current" "Magnet" "Paper cone (Diaphragm)"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.28,0:25:21.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Sending your voice with electricity...\NWhat a great idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.62,0:25:26.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Bell wanted to find a way to help\Ndeaf people hear. That's how he thought of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.50,0:25:30.09,Main,,0,0,0,,So science can give form\Nto people's feelings too, huh?
